.TH HSH 1 "December 2023" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter. It reads commands from standard input and executes them.

.SH FEATURES
.IP \[bu]
Executes commands with arguments
.IP \[bu]
Handles the PATH environment variable
.IP \[bu]
Implements built-in commands: exit, env
.IP \[bu]
Supports both interactive and non-interactive mode

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic command:
.B $ ls
.TP
Command with arguments:
.B $ ls -l
.TP
Using PATH:
.B $ pwd

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 127
Command not found

.SH AUTHOR
Frederic Bourouliou <frederic.bourouliou@gmail.com>

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh(1) 